import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('state')['zip_code'].count().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='state', y='zip_code', data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes across different states?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
